    <h1>Connect Javascript with Flask</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>In this article, we want to explain briefly how we connect Javas=
cript with Flask for realizing concrete usecases. Note that due to the dyna=
mical UX which responds reactively to user events, it is not sufficient to =
work only with<br>Jinja2. We thus invoke some Vanilla Javascript.</p>
<p>A sample usecase is changing the selected material type (e.g. when creat=
ing base materials or blended materials). This requires only parts of the U=
X to be updated. Therefore, on a given page, we have several templates for =
self-contained parts of the UI. These can be requested from the backend and=
 dynamically rendered into the UI by adjusting the html based on the backen=
d's response. If we were to re-render the complete page, this would amount =
to deleting previously configured input which we do not want.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Technically, the above can be achieved by returning a json response with=
 a key (in our case called 'template') with the value given by the specific=
 html file we are interested in. An example is provided in the following co=
de:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">@base_m=
aterials.route('/&lt;type&gt;', methods=3D['GET'])
def select_base_material_type(type):
    template_file, form =3D base_materials_service.create_material_form(typ=
e)
    body =3D {'template': render_template(template_file, form=3Dform)}
    return make_response(jsonify(body), 200)</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Here form referers to the specific WTForm we are rendering into the temp=
late_file (e.g. a PowderForm() is used in powder_form.py).</p>
<p>The corresonding Javascript looks as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">functio=
n selectMaterialType() {
    const elem =3D document.getElementById("material_type");
    const url =3D `${BASE_MATERIALS_URL}/${elem.value.toLowerCase()}`;
    fetchEmbedTemplateInPlaceholder(url, "template-placeholder");
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>Here we call the fetchEmbedTemplateInPlaceholder method which executes t=
he backend call and renders the response into an html tag with id "template=
-placeholder". Note that internally, the fetchEmbedTemplateInPlaceholder&nb=
sp; call is asynchronous and waits for the response before the rendering is=
 executed.</p>
    </div>
